Israeli Stocks: Bio Light, Ormat and Ratio Oil Exploration

-- B y   R o n i t   G o o d m a n
-- 
2011-02-23T11:53:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-23/israeli-stocks-bio-light-ormat-and-ratio-oil-exploration.html
  Israel ’s TA-25 Index dropped for a
third day, slipping 0.2 percent to 1,312.02 at 1:35 p.m. in Tel
Aviv.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.    Bio Light Israeli Life Sciences Investments Ltd . (BOLT IT)
gained for the first time in five days, increasing 1.8 percent
to 0.39 shekel. The owner of companies that develop drugs and
medical technology said it will issue about 31.3 million shares
to an investor group led by Israel Makov and an additional 7.4
million shares to other investors.    Ormat Industries  Ltd. (ORMT IT) fell to the lowest level
since Nov. 30, dropping 2.1 percent to 27.91 shekels. The
builder and operator said it will report a loss for the fourth
quarter and all of 2010 after a writedown of the value of a
unit’s power station.    Ratio Oil Exploration 1992 LP  (RATIL IT) increased to the
highest since Feb. 10, advancing 7.5 percent to 0.618 shekel.
Barclays Capital said the full potential of the Leviathan
discovery isn’t priced into shares of the explorer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ronit Goodman in Tel Aviv at 
